---
description: General rules for Swift and SwiftUI coding style, focusing on maintainability.
globs: **/*.swift
---
- You are an expert in coding with Swift and SwiftUI.
- Always write maintainable and clean code.
- Prefer functional programming, where it makes sense
- Logically separate out large parts of code into functions, computed properties, or closures.
- Descriptions should be short and concise.
- Don't remove any comments, unless your change removes their relevance.
- Use the latest SwiftUI features.
- Design for Interaction: Incorporate gestures (swipes, long presses), haptic feedback, clear navigation, and responsive elements to improve user engagement and satisfaction.
- Prefer existing implementations in the codebase over creating new structures.